My bubble tea dreams are coming true 🥹💕 I’ve been absolutely OBSESSED with @thealley.usa  for years— and the best part? Now that @thealleyportland is finally opening in Portland this Saturday 5/24! 🎉

If you know, you know: The Alley isn’t just bubble tea, it’s an experience. From their iconic brown sugar Deerioca series 🦌 to perfectly balanced milk teas and fruit blends, everything is crafted with serious love and flavor.

📍Grand Opening this Saturday — Don’t Miss It!
✨ Expect great sweets, cute vibes, and drinks worth the hype
📸 Pro tip: Grab 1 of the Brown Sugar Boba Series with Croffle and thank me later 😍

📌10542 SE Washington St Portland, Oregon 

#Thankyou @thealleyportland for inviting and treating your wonderful drinks and croffles 🫶

We just experienced the bold, fiery flavors of Isan food at @zabpintothai last night 🇹🇭🍴 It was a 🔥 deep dive into the bold, spicy flavors of Thailand’s Northeast — and I’m still thinking about every bite.

Truly one of the most authentic and heartwarming Thai dinners I’ve had in Portland 🫶

We feasted on:
🥩 Larb Koii (raw beef done right!)
🐷 Kor Moo Yang — perfectly grilled pork
🌶️ Somtum Lao-style — spicy, funky, addictive
🐟 Miang Pla — so fresh and full of herbs
🍖 Tom Zab with pork short ribs — sour, spicy, comforting
🥭 Mango sticky rice — the sweetest ending 💛

But don’t worry — if Isan heat isn’t your thing, @zabpintothai also serves classic Thai dishes you already love. Think comforting curries, pad thai, and more 🙌

📌1037 NW Flanders St, Portland, OR 97209

Huge thanks to chef Malvin, @zabpintothai , and all staffs for the passion, flavors, and hospitality 🙏
